  "description": "morphGlide=1.0 (maximum possible). portamento=0.95 (extremely slow). bodyFreq=110Hz (A1 — an octave above the standard A habitat; brighter, more present). When you play legato, the metamorphosis takes so long to complete that it becomes the texture itself. The destination note is never fully reached before the next note triggers. This is not portamento — it is a continuous becoming. Even dividers ÷2, ÷4 keep the harmonic world stable while the pitch world dissolves.",
